# Approach
We can fix the first number ( say x) then the second number must be in between [lower - x , upper - x].
To get above result, we need to sort the array and then find the upper bound of (upper - nums[i]) and lower bound of (lower - nums[i]).
Difference of the upper bound index and lower bound index will give us the number elements that can be added to nums[i] whose sum will be in between lower & upper.

```
class Solution {
public:
    long long countFairPairs(vector<int>& nums, int lower, int upper) {
        long long ans = 0;
        auto beg = nums.begin(), end = nums.end();
        sort(beg, end);
        for(int i = 0; i < nums.size()-1; ++i){
            ans += upper_bound(beg + i+1, end, upper - nums[i]) - lower_bound(beg + i+1, end, lower - nums[i]);
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```

