# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Here, I use binary search approch to find the correct index range of ans for every element of the given array using binary search.
The length of the range will add up to our final answer.


# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
    O(nlogn) where n is the number of elements in the array.
- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
    O(1)

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    long long countPairSum(vector<int>& arr,int l,int r){
        sort(arr.begin(),arr.end());    
        int n=arr.size();
        long long right = n-1, ans = 0;

        while (right > 0) {
            // finding starting point of range
            long long strt = lower_bound(arr.begin(), arr .end(),l - arr[right])-arr.begin();

            // finding ending point of range
            auto it2 = upper_bound(arr.begin(), arr .end(), r - arr[right]);
            --it2;
            long long end = it2 - arr.begin();

            end = min(end, right - 1);

            // adding length of the range to our final answer.
            if (end - strt >= 0)
                ans += (end - strt + 1);

            right--;
        }
        return ans;
    }

    long long countFairPairs(vector<int>& nums, int lower, int upper) {
        long long ans = countPairSum(nums,lower,upper);
        return ans;
    }
};
```

