# Intuition
Similar to 3 sum problem. We have fix one number and find other possible number in logn, building base for sorting. 

# Approach
I fixed all element once, in remaining array obtain the lower value and upper value which we need to find in the array. We need sorting array for this.
eg. fixed number is 3, lower=1, upper=4
we need to find number of element between -2(lower-fixed number) and  4(upper-fixed number)

For this i created two helper function , using binary search 
upppervalue: telling the index just greater than required by upper element finded by us. 
lowervalue:telling the index just smaller than required by lower element finded by us. 

We can take all element between index founded by helper function.

special case: if i also forms a part of of index range , then we have to exclude it , as we cannot take same number twice.


 At last we half our ans because of contraint i<j as we have included cases where j>i;

# Complexity
- Time complexity:O(nlogn)

- Space complexity:O(1)

